{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":888,"text":"There's a big question\nat the center of life"},{"time":3046,"text":"in our democracies today:"},{"time":4984,"text":"How do we fight terror\nwithout destroying democracies,"},{"time":8353,"text":"without trampling human rights?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":11594,"text":"I've spent much of my career\nworking with journalists,"},{"time":16213,"text":"with bloggers,"},{"time":17395,"text":"with activists,"},{"time":18733,"text":"with human rights researchers\nall around the world,"},{"time":21372,"text":"and I've come to the conclusion"},{"time":23506,"text":"that if our democratic societies\ndo not double down"},{"time":28175,"text":"on protecting and defending human rights,"},{"time":31182,"text":"freedom of the press"},{"time":32606,"text":"and a free and open internet,"},{"time":35932,"text":"radical extremist ideologies\nare much more likely to persist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42537,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":45006,"text":"OK, all done. Thank you very much."},{"time":46714,"text":"No, just joking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47897,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":49716,"text":"I actually want to drill down\non this a little bit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52965,"text":"So, one of the countries that has been\non the frontlines of this issue"},{"time":58736,"text":"is Tunisia,"},{"time":60325,"text":"which was the only country\nto come out of the Arab Spring"},{"time":63865,"text":"with a successful democratic revolution."},{"time":66967,"text":"Five years later,"},{"time":68256,"text":"they're struggling\nwith serious terror attacks"},{"time":71116,"text":"and rampant ISIS recruitment."},{"time":73853,"text":"And many Tunisians\nare calling on their government"},{"time":76661,"text":"to do whatever it takes to keep them safe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80686,"text":"Tunisian cartoonist Nadia Khiari"},{"time":83738,"text":"has summed up the situation\nwith this character who says,"},{"time":88037,"text":"\"I don't give a damn about human rights."},{"time":90640,"text":"I don't give a damn about the revolution."},{"time":93515,"text":"I don't give a damn\nabout democracy and liberty."},{"time":97587,"text":"I just want to be safe.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":101672,"text":"\"Satisfied?\" asked his jailer."},{"time":104896,"text":"\"You're safe now.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":106941,"text":"If the Tunisian people can figure out"},{"time":109720,"text":"how to deal with their terrorism problem"},{"time":111807,"text":"without ending up in this place,"},{"time":114771,"text":"they will be a model\nnot only for their region,"},{"time":117478,"text":"but for all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120402,"text":"The reality is that civil society,\njournalists and activists"},{"time":124462,"text":"are coming under attack\nfrom extremist groups on the one hand,"},{"time":129315,"text":"and, in many countries,"},{"time":131069,"text":"also from their own governments."},{"time":133528,"text":"We're seeing bloggers\nand journalists being jailed,"},{"time":136944,"text":"charged and intimidated"},{"time":138406,"text":"by their own governments,"},{"time":139948,"text":"many of which are allies\nwith the West in the war on terror."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143785,"text":"Just three examples."},{"time":145446,"text":"A friend and former colleague of mine,"},{"time":147326,"text":"Hisham Almiraat,"},{"time":148582,"text":"has been charged\nwith threatening state security,"},{"time":151650,"text":"along with six other activists in Morocco."},{"time":155144,"text":"The Saudi blogger Raif Badawi\nhas been jailed and flogged"},{"time":159641,"text":"for insulting Islam and criticizing\nthe Saudi regime on his blog."},{"time":165437,"text":"More recently, the Turkish representative\nfor Reporters Without Borders,"},{"time":170951,"text":"Erol Ã–nderoglu,"},{"time":172822,"text":"has been detained and charged\nwith spreading terrorist propaganda,"},{"time":177590,"text":"because he and some other activists\nhave been supporting Kurdish media."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183025,"text":"Anti-terror measures\nquickly turn into state repression"},{"time":186736,"text":"without strong protection\nfor minority communities"},{"time":190297,"text":"and for peaceful debate;"},{"time":192729,"text":"this needs to be supported\nby a robust, independent local media."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197749,"text":"But while that's not really happening,"},{"time":200077,"text":"Washington is teaming up\nwith Silicon Valley and with Hollywood"},{"time":204701,"text":"to pour millions -- hundreds\nof millions of dollars --"},{"time":209101,"text":"into what's called \"counter-messaging,\""},{"time":211712,"text":"a fancy word for propaganda."},{"time":214154,"text":"To counter the terrorist propaganda\nspreading all over the internet,"},{"time":220614,"text":"in Europe, Internet Referral\nUnits are being set up,"},{"time":224384,"text":"so that people can report\non extremist content that they find"},{"time":228385,"text":"and get it censored."},{"time":230191,"text":"The problem is,"},{"time":231575,"text":"that all of this propaganda,\nmonitoring and censorship"},{"time":236204,"text":"completely fails to make up for the fact"},{"time":241236,"text":"that the people who are\nthe most credible voices,"},{"time":246334,"text":"who can present credible ideas\nand alternative solutions"},{"time":250443,"text":"to real economic, social and political\nproblems in their community"},{"time":254568,"text":"that are causing people to turn\nto extremism in the first place,"},{"time":258875,"text":"are being silenced\nby their own governments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262214,"text":"This is all adding up to a decrease\nin freedom across the world."},{"time":267801,"text":"Freedom House,"},{"time":269001,"text":"the human rights organization,"},{"time":271055,"text":"reports that 2015 marks\nthe 10th straight year in a row"},{"time":275415,"text":"of decline in freedom worldwide."},{"time":278495,"text":"And this is not just\nbecause of the actions"},{"time":280915,"text":"of authoritarian governments."},{"time":282970,"text":"It's also because democratic governments"},{"time":285491,"text":"are increasingly cracking\ndown on dissenters,"},{"time":289818,"text":"whistle-blowers"},{"time":291010,"text":"and investigative journalists."},{"time":292947,"text":"UN Secretary General\nBan Ki-Moon has warned"},{"time":295405,"text":"that \"preventing extremism and promoting\nhuman rights go hand-in-hand.\""},{"time":299866,"text":"It's not to say that governments\nshouldn't keep us safe --"},{"time":302694,"text":"of course they should --"},{"time":303869,"text":"but we need public oversight, transparency"},{"time":306488,"text":"and accountability to the rule of law."},{"time":308753,"text":"Meanwhile,"},{"time":309929,"text":"extremists are literally killing off\ncivil society in some countries."},{"time":314198,"text":"Since 2013 in Bangladesh,"},{"time":316756,"text":"over a dozen secular bloggers\nand community activists"},{"time":321296,"text":"have been literally\nslaughtered by extremists"},{"time":324253,"text":"while the government has done very little."},{"time":327008,"text":"From the city of Raqqa in Syria,"},{"time":329979,"text":"people like Ruqia Hassan and Naji Jerf\nhave been assassinated"},{"time":334579,"text":"for their reporting\nout of ISIS-controlled territory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338315,"text":"The citizen media group called\nRaqqa is Being Slaughtered Silently"},{"time":343923,"text":"relies on strong encryption\nto send out their reports"},{"time":348166,"text":"and shield themselves\nfrom interception and surveillance."},{"time":352057,"text":"Yet authorities in countries\nlike the United States,"},{"time":354831,"text":"the United Kingdom\nand many other democracies"},{"time":357398,"text":"are seeking to use the law"},{"time":359275,"text":"to either weaken or outright ban\nstrong encryption,"},{"time":363756,"text":"because the bad guys are using it, too."},{"time":366465,"text":"We have got to fight for the right\nof citizens to use strong encryption."},{"time":370749,"text":"Otherwise, dissent\nand investigative journalism"},{"time":374403,"text":"are going to become even more difficult"},{"time":376826,"text":"in even more places."},{"time":378654,"text":"And the bad guys -- the criminals\nand terrorists --"},{"time":381149,"text":"are still going to find\nways to communicate."},{"time":383433,"text":"Kudos to the companies\nthat are standing up"},{"time":386096,"text":"for their users' right to use encryption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389595,"text":"But when it comes to censorship,"},{"time":391885,"text":"the picture is much more troubling."},{"time":394610,"text":"Yes, there's a real problem"},{"time":396452,"text":"of extremist content\nspreading all over the internet."},{"time":399739,"text":"And Facebook, YouTube and Twitter\nare among the many companies"},{"time":403296,"text":"who report having taken down hundreds\nof thousands of pieces of content"},{"time":407747,"text":"and deactivating accounts"},{"time":409351,"text":"that are connected\nto the extremist's speech."},{"time":411855,"text":"The problem is their enforcement\nmechanisms are a complete black box,"},{"time":416199,"text":"and there is collateral damage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418211,"text":"Take, for example, Iyad el-Baghdadi,"},{"time":421516,"text":"an activist who makes fun\nof ISIS on Twitter."},{"time":424176,"text":"He had his account deactivated,"},{"time":426016,"text":"because he shares a surname\nwith a prominent ISIS leader."},{"time":430220,"text":"Last December,"},{"time":431395,"text":"a number of women named Isis,"},{"time":433038,"text":"which also happens to be\nthe name of an Egyptian goddess,"},{"time":436514,"text":"had their accounts deactivated."},{"time":438742,"text":"And this woman,"},{"time":440382,"text":"who lives in the United States\nand is a computer programmer,"},{"time":443511,"text":"reported on Twitter\nabout her deactivation on Facebook,"},{"time":447261,"text":"managed to get enough media attention\nto have her account reinstated."},{"time":450978,"text":"But that's the thing --\nshe had to get media attention."},{"time":454020,"text":"And journalists aren't immune."},{"time":455553,"text":"David Thomson,"},{"time":456751,"text":"an expert on terrorism and reporter\nfor Radio France International,"},{"time":460173,"text":"had reports deleted\nfrom his Facebook account"},{"time":463760,"text":"and had his account\ndeactivated for several days,"},{"time":466573,"text":"because they contained\npictures of ISIS flags,"},{"time":470498,"text":"even though he was just reporting on ISIS,"},{"time":472578,"text":"not promoting it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474253,"text":"And then we have stories from people\nlike this Egyptian man,"},{"time":477266,"text":"Ahmed Abdellahy,"},{"time":478907,"text":"who reported recently in an event\nin Washington DC"},{"time":484074,"text":"that some of his arguments\nwith extremists --"},{"time":486272,"text":"he now spends his time on social media\narguing with ISIS followers,"},{"time":492609,"text":"trying to get them to turn away --"},{"time":495141,"text":"some of his arguments\nwith these extremists get deleted,"},{"time":500160,"text":"which he believes has the effect\nof shielding them"},{"time":503231,"text":"from alternative points of view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506217,"text":"It's unclear whether Facebook\neven knows the extent"},{"time":510626,"text":"of the collateral damage,"},{"time":512162,"text":"or the other companies as well."},{"time":514558,"text":"But we do know that journalism,\nactivism and public debate"},{"time":518196,"text":"are being silenced in the effort\nto stamp out extremist speech."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523398,"text":"So with these companies having so much\npower over the public discourse,"},{"time":527663,"text":"they need to be held accountable."},{"time":529281,"text":"They need to carry out impact assessment"},{"time":532186,"text":"to identify and fix the problems\nthat we're clearly seeing."},{"time":536727,"text":"They need to be more transparent\nabout their enforcement mechanisms,"},{"time":540527,"text":"and they need to have clear\nappeal and grievance mechanisms,"},{"time":543953,"text":"so people can get\ntheir content reinstated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546640,"text":"Now, I've been talking\nfor the last 10 minutes"},{"time":549857,"text":"about how governments and companies\nare making it more difficult"},{"time":553996,"text":"for people like these."},{"time":555356,"text":"This is a picture of members\nof the citizen media network,"},{"time":558863,"text":"Global Voices,"},{"time":560038,"text":"that I helped to cofound over 10 years ago"},{"time":562155,"text":"with my friend, Ethan Zuckerman."},{"time":564175,"text":"Interestingly, about 5 years ago,\nright after the Arab Spring,"},{"time":568669,"text":"the data scientist Gilad Lotan"},{"time":571350,"text":"created a network map\nof the people in Global Voices"},{"time":576291,"text":"who were heavy users of Twitter\nduring the Arab Spring."},{"time":579237,"text":"And he found that many of these people\nserved as key information nodes"},{"time":584479,"text":"between activists and journalists"},{"time":586367,"text":"throughout the Tunisian\nand Egyptian revolution."},{"time":589416,"text":"We've got to make sure\nthat these people not only survive,"},{"time":594706,"text":"but are able to continue to thrive."},{"time":597216,"text":"Many of them are still active,"},{"time":598894,"text":"other than the ones who have gone to jail"},{"time":600994,"text":"or have been driven into hiding or exile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604668,"text":"All around the world,"},{"time":606510,"text":"people who are sick and tired\nof fear and oppression"},{"time":609851,"text":"are linking up in their communities\nand across borders."},{"time":613325,"text":"We've got to do everything we can\nto push our governments and companies"},{"time":617612,"text":"to do a better job\nof protecting their rights."},{"time":620572,"text":"We've also got to be more mindful"},{"time":622581,"text":"about how our own personal, political,\nconsumer and business choices"},{"time":627450,"text":"affect people like these around the world."},{"time":631112,"text":"Also, if you follow the news,"},{"time":633568,"text":"it's pretty clear that that alone\nisn't going to be enough."},{"time":637694,"text":"We've got to take personal\nresponsibility by joining --"},{"time":641478,"text":"or at very least, actively supporting --"},{"time":644919,"text":"the growing ecosystem\nof individuals and groups"},{"time":648464,"text":"who are fighting for social justice,"},{"time":650574,"text":"environmental sustainability,"},{"time":652661,"text":"government accountability,"},{"time":654248,"text":"human rights, freedom of the press"},{"time":656149,"text":"and a free and open internet,"},{"time":657729,"text":"all around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659509,"text":"I believe that, ultimately,\nwe can overcome"},{"time":664244,"text":"the digitally empowered networks\nof extremism, demagoguery and hate."},{"time":671379,"text":"But ..."},{"time":673104,"text":"we've got to do this by really\nbeefing up the global networks"},{"time":679852,"text":"of citizens around the world,"},{"time":681664,"text":"powered by people\nwho are working hard every day,"},{"time":685468,"text":"and taking personal risk"},{"time":687714,"text":"for a future world that is more\npeaceful, just, open and free."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693541,"text":"Thanks very much for listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695094,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}